<subSubSection id="9F2AF419F6FAA683B196D67784865113" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5555B613C06F0B763FAA95C74959074E" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2194385A21E50D082847E3C5E191E9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
The name is an anagram of the sister genus 
<taxonomicName id="9F37B5D8C47D11B219A8FB94BB0B3CEA" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Orbamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orbamia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EF367F26B0DC26A92DE0B4EAB4C14A39" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Orbamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, similarly to the anagram used by 
<bibRefCitation id="63882E8DB5FD3A323730EAC1226ABCAB" author="Herbulot, C" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin Mensuel Societe Linneenne de Lyon" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="216 - 221" refId="B12" refString="Herbulot, C, 1966. Nouveaux Geometridae du Sud-ouest de Madagascar. Bulletin Mensuel Societe Linneenne de Lyon 35: 216 - 221" title="Nouveaux Geometridae du Sud-ouest de Madagascar." volume="35" year="1966">Herbulot (1966)</bibRefCitation>
when transforming the name 
<taxonomicName id="8A828818C6A4D5A13BC071A20EAE422F" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Boarmia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boarmia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C50384D4348D53AF95C14A53AE01FE63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Boarmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="FFBA371F73DC96118935D7C295B08006" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Orbamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orbamia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F87AF7402962BF4E863158CCD51D849A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Orbamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="72E262A97B35A558575CF277E0A01979" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="differential features">
<paragraph id="B3516DB306C520ECCBF7490AD917DD77" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Differential features</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7873B959084F1358A4FDA86F25F10C2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">(COI sequences, photographs of adults and their genitalia see https://dx.doi.org/10.5883/DS-ORBAMIA). Adult: Male antennae ciliate-fasciculate, female antennae filiform. Palpi of both sexes broad, bushy scaled, length 1.0-1.5 times diameter of eye. Hind tibia of both sexes with two pairs of unequal spurs. Upperside of wings with discal spots vestigial, medial line zigzagging, terminal line conspicuous, zigzagging on all wings. Underside beige, with a few yellowish scales and a sharp black spot in forewing apex. Male genitalia: Uncus very short, rounded saccus shallowly projecting, dorsal process of valva strongly setose, valva long and narrow, curved, strongly setose, mainly at centre, aedeagus with long and stout cornutus. Female genitalia: Apophyses long and fine. Lamellae ante- and post-vaginalis membranous, ductus bursae straight, anteriorly membranous, posteriorly dilated and towards antrum strongly sclerotised, corpus bursae membranous, pyriform, signum absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D256DD5A77FCEEEA705D4BB64004CC30" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="genetic data and phylogeny">
<paragraph id="ED85E2FA075778B8FA8A34FE16DE13F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Genetic data and phylogeny.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6714EE9F4C7B4EAFCA90F673EBD6D667" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
The maximum likelihood analysis of COI barcode data suggests the monophyly of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="98AB98EEDE00633CB8252A0CC283296B" authority="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba, 2020" authorityName="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Morabia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Morabia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E136687D353BC3C4B1A5EAA58D9940DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Morabia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. and an isolated position from (
<taxonomicName id="612D7BE43F8C4F47895E69953A988831" authority="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba, 2020" authorityName="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Rabomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rabomia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1E6AA7D97D4B6DD756432FD3F4A61783" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Rabomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. (
<taxonomicName id="9791FDBD3DF1E90057276262B0C0EBBC" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pycnostega" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pycnostega" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="527DB6586F45ACAB85AA1A692E27EFF4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Pycnostega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="F774C6E1441F9250D4F9E811FF375B69" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Dorsifulcrum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorsifulcrum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AAD56AAFF7FCA976A521AB877375B358" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Dorsifulcrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)) and from genus 
<taxonomicName id="43CD7B6CF2521348C044E6398A212E5C" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Orbamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orbamia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3979FBDD51BE52EAF12D6CCD015C8555" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Orbamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. Table 
<tableCitation id="55276959B7BC1629189E1674797A91D4" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Barcode gap analysis of COI data of the genera Orbamia, Rabomia, and Morabia (https: // dx. doi. org / 10.5883 / DS-ORBAMIA), showing intraspecific variation (&quot; Mean Intra-Sp &quot; and &quot; Max. Intra-Sp. &quot;) and distances from Nearest Neighbour Species (&quot; NN &quot;)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5D9BF46CEBC36B6C506BFCB1111E5C75" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" tableUuid="5D9BF46CEBC36B6C506BFCB1111E5C75">1</tableCitation>
, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ADE94F3277868C8808928E51263FEDFC" captionStart="Figure 85" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 85. Maximum Likelihood Tree of COI data of the genera Orbamia, Rabomia, and Morabia, 50 Bootstrap Replications, Tamura-Nei model, uniform rates, built with Mega 6 software (Tamura et al. 2013; scale bar = 2 %), for original data see https: // dx. doi. org / 10.5883 / DS-ORBAMIA." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.50391.figure85" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402627" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">85</figureCitation>
). However, phylogenies at genus level need to be considered with caution, when they are inferred from COI data.
</paragraph>
